  <brief_title>Study of Sildenafil in Patient With Heart Failure.</brief_title>
  <official_title>Measurement of the Effect of Sildenafil Citrate (Viagra) on the Hemodynamics of Exercise Tolerance in Advanced Congestive Heart Failure.</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Massachusetts General Hospital</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Massachusetts General Hospital</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine if sildenafil (Viagra) improves exercise tolerance.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Patients will undergo an exercise stress test. One dose of Sildenafil will then be given,
      followed by a one hour rest period. A repeat exercise stress test will then be repeated.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
